cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is about attribute-based recognition models in computer vision, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with image and video analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques to discover and learn semantic attributes, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of deep learning models for optimization and association estimation makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed model on large-scale datasets involving image and video analysis suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
